snippet.textDisplay:
It’s so unfortunate how packaged everything at Trader Joe’s is. Which sucks cause their stuff is amazing and priced really well.
Whole Foods has far less packaging but still WAY more than necessary and it’s owned by Amazon, who paid $0 in income tax last year.
In order to stop our earth from becoming unlivable, we have to cut down on plastic WAYYYYY more than we have been, but how can we do that if every zero waste store or alternative is not only incredibly expensive, but also inaccessible to SO many? I can’t see a way out of this mess we got ourselves in, but I commend you Morgan for taking this challenge. It takes so much water and energy to produce meat and dairy.

snippet.textDisplay: I went vegan 2 and a half years ago and lost 5 pounds a month for a year. So I went from 200 pounds to 140 pounds in a year. I had been 200 and a size 16 from 14 years old-22 years old, and accepted that as my natural body. Now i've been between 140 and 150 for almost 3 years and i don't even work out. My face has like a centimeter less of just thickness around it, full of oil and toxins. Anyways, it's become more and more spiritual for me and has helped a lot with low self-esteem because i'm proud of myself and my choices. I feel a connection and respect for everything, it feels harmonious almost, like it's the way it's supposed to be. And my conscience definitely spoke to me when i went against it, and i think that's powerful. It's one of the best decisions I've ever made physically and mentally.

snippet.textDisplay: Can’t go vegan because I’m constantly worried about getting enough proteins. I have the sweetener/gluten free vegetable based protein shake powder, but I got tired of it and missed chicken/turkey/eggs/fish. I tried being a pescatarian but preparing chicken/turkey is so easy. No red meat keeps my cholesterol in check. Put a little lean chicken/turkey breast & avocado on a salad and you have a balanced meal. Can’t beat convenience.
